  "notes": "Per-hole data transcribed directly from the club's official scorecard PDF (tarjeta-del-campo.pdf, June 2023), read as an image; every nine and 18-hole total sums exactly to the printed IDA/VUELTA/TOTALES (Blancas 3264+2576=5840, Amarillas 3158+2498=5656, Azules 2831+2272=5103, Rojas 2723+2191=4914), par 37+34=71, and stroke indexes are a valid 1-18 permutation. Cross-checked against the RFEG club page, which confirms par 71, the four tee sets, and near-identical ratings. Ratings on the printed card are Blancas 71.4/130 and Amarillas 70.4/127 (men) and Azules 73.1/131 and Rojas 71.8/129 (women), used here; the other-gender ratings (Blancas/Amarillas women 77.6/143 and 76.1/140, Azules/Rojas men 67.2/122 and 66.3/120) come from RFEG. Discrepancies: RFEG lists slightly different rated lengths (Blancas 5873, Amarillas 5635, Azules 5075, Rojas 4884) with a few holes differing from the card (e.g. hole 8 Blancas 115 vs 132, hole 9 Blancas 631 vs 562, hole 18 Blancas 452 vs 471), and marginally different ratings for the card-published genders (Blancas M 71.4/129, Amarillas M 70.2/126, Azules F 72.7/132, Rojas F 71.5/130) - likely a different rating vintage/marker position; the official card was preferred for distances. RFEG additionally rates an alternative par-72 configuration in which hole 9 (El Largo) plays as a par 6 (~644 m from Blancas; totals 5886/5714/5161/4967) - not included here since the standard tarjeta is par 71. Amarillas mapped to color \"gold\" (yellow not available)."
